03/06/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The OSCE mission to Croatia urged the government Wednesday (2 June) to enhance human rights protections. Key steps recommended by the OSCE include strengthening of domestic institutions and harmonising legislation with the European Convention on Human Rights.
Also Wednesday, border police chiefs from Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Macedonia, Romania, Turkey and Serbia-Montenegro met in Rakitje near Zagreb. They discussed co-operation initiatives and reforms. (OSCE press release, HINA - 02/06/04)
